00:12:48.030 --> 00:12:48.910 align:middle line:90%
Welcome back.

00:12:48.910 --> 00:12:52.950 align:middle line:84%
I'm talking with Professor
Huston Smith about the fate

00:12:52.950 --> 00:12:57.110 align:middle line:84%
and the future of the human
spirit in an age of disbelief.

00:12:57.110 --> 00:13:00.030 align:middle line:84%
And I think, Huston, the
issue we were touching on

00:13:00.030 --> 00:13:03.360 align:middle line:84%
before the break
is even a stronger

00:13:03.360 --> 00:13:05.700 align:middle line:84%
issue than the
scientific argument,

00:13:05.700 --> 00:13:09.570 align:middle line:84%
actually, that people
may resort to science,

00:13:09.570 --> 00:13:12.950 align:middle line:84%
but it's because in some sense
they feel let down by God.

00:13:12.950 --> 00:13:13.950 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:13:13.950 --> 00:13:16.980 align:middle line:84%
I'm glad you went
back to that anecdote

00:13:16.980 --> 00:13:23.520 align:middle line:84%
because, in the same way, I had
an experience which sort of put

00:13:23.520 --> 00:13:26.190 align:middle line:90%
a bookend onto this.

00:13:26.190 --> 00:13:32.250 align:middle line:84%
I was being driven to a
program in San Francisco,

00:13:32.250 --> 00:13:36.800 align:middle line:84%
and my driver had been on
Stephen Gaskin's "The Farm."

00:13:36.800 --> 00:13:39.420 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes, and he was a--

00:13:39.420 --> 00:13:41.050 align:middle line:90%
one might say a cult leader or--

00:13:41.050 --> 00:13:41.850 align:middle line:90%
>> A cult leader?

00:13:41.850 --> 00:13:42.615 align:middle line:90%
>> --a philosopher--

00:13:42.615 --> 00:13:43.415 align:middle line:90%
>> And a--

00:13:43.415 --> 00:13:45.660 align:middle line:84%
>> --who became a religious
leader back in the '70s.

00:13:45.660 --> 00:13:48.480 align:middle line:84%
>> Exactly, and
it's been a really--

00:13:48.480 --> 00:13:52.410 align:middle line:84%
on the whole, a very
successful utopian community,

00:13:52.410 --> 00:13:54.270 align:middle line:84%
but to come to the
point, they had

00:13:54.270 --> 00:13:57.060 align:middle line:84%
to try to be
self-sufficient, and he

00:13:57.060 --> 00:14:00.120 align:middle line:90%
was assigned refrigeration.

00:14:00.120 --> 00:14:04.530 align:middle line:84%
Now, he hadn't even been past
the fourth grade, and all

00:14:04.530 --> 00:14:07.470 align:middle line:84%
these diagrams of
electrical circuits,

00:14:07.470 --> 00:14:09.130 align:middle line:90%
he couldn't figure it out.

00:14:09.130 --> 00:14:11.050 align:middle line:90%
So he went to a professional.

00:14:11.050 --> 00:14:16.230 align:middle line:84%
The professional explained
it, and so Rob left and said,

00:14:16.230 --> 00:14:17.950 align:middle line:90%
I think I've got it.

00:14:17.950 --> 00:14:21.000 align:middle line:84%
And as he went out the
door, the professional

00:14:21.000 --> 00:14:22.830 align:middle line:90%
hollered after him--

00:14:22.830 --> 00:14:25.440 align:middle line:90%
this is Tennessee, remember--

00:14:25.440 --> 00:14:28.560 align:middle line:90%
don't let it whop you.

00:14:28.560 --> 00:14:33.540 align:middle line:84%
And when I match that against
these two experiences of the,

00:14:33.540 --> 00:14:36.960 align:middle line:90%
it don't make sense, does it?

00:14:36.960 --> 00:14:40.170 align:middle line:84%
And when you look
around, that's right,

00:14:40.170 --> 00:14:43.410 align:middle line:84%
and you're picking up on
that point-- for so many,

00:14:43.410 --> 00:14:45.210 align:middle line:90%
it just doesn't make sense.

00:14:45.210 --> 00:14:51.100 align:middle line:84%
But I think the religious answer
is, but don't let it whop you.

00:14:51.100 --> 00:14:55.480 align:middle line:84%
And so those are the bookends
of our everyday experience.

00:14:55.480 --> 00:14:57.070 align:middle line:90%
>> Mm-hmm.

00:14:57.070 --> 00:14:59.570 align:middle line:84%
Well, they say what doesn't
kill you will make you stronger.

00:14:59.570 --> 00:15:00.720 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:15:00.720 --> 00:15:02.480 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:15:02.480 --> 00:15:05.960 align:middle line:84%
>> And you use a very
interesting metaphor.

00:15:05.960 --> 00:15:11.660 align:middle line:84%
You say when a child spills
their ice cream cone,

00:15:11.660 --> 00:15:13.790 align:middle line:84%
it may seem like the
end of the world.

00:15:13.790 --> 00:15:14.870 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:15:14.870 --> 00:15:17.520 align:middle line:84%
>> But the parent has a
different perspective.

00:15:17.520 --> 00:15:21.170 align:middle line:84%
>> And I think it really
comes down to that.

00:15:21.170 --> 00:15:24.470 align:middle line:90%
How large is our perspective?

00:15:24.470 --> 00:15:31.590 align:middle line:84%
Because if we let it be confined
by this three-dimensional

00:15:31.590 --> 00:15:37.250 align:middle line:84%
world, and all the craziness,
and injustice, and so on--

00:15:37.250 --> 00:15:40.890 align:middle line:84%
if that's all we see,
it's absolutely right.

00:15:40.890 --> 00:15:42.930 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't make any sense.

00:15:42.930 --> 00:15:47.400 align:middle line:84%
But just as in a great
painting, if you were just

00:15:47.400 --> 00:15:53.650 align:middle line:84%
to blot out everything but a 6
by 6-inch square and some maybe

00:15:53.650 --> 00:15:58.410 align:middle line:84%
muddy colors there, and that's
all you saw, why, of course,

00:15:58.410 --> 00:16:00.230 align:middle line:90%
there'd be no beauty there.

00:16:00.230 --> 00:16:05.765 align:middle line:84%
But if you enlarge
the horizon, and then

00:16:05.765 --> 00:16:10.130 align:middle line:84%
that actually
doubles back to show

00:16:10.130 --> 00:16:15.840 align:middle line:84%
how that little area that didn't
mean much in itself actually

00:16:15.840 --> 00:16:18.150 align:middle line:90%
contributes to the whole.

00:16:18.150 --> 00:16:18.950 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:16:18.950 --> 00:16:21.560 align:middle line:84%
That seems to be right
there encapsulated,

00:16:21.560 --> 00:16:26.090 align:middle line:84%
your fundamental argument
about the role of spirit.

00:16:26.090 --> 00:16:30.680 align:middle line:84%
It's-- is the wholeness that
makes our lives meaningful.

00:16:30.680 --> 00:16:33.500 align:middle line:90%
>> That's exactly right.

00:16:33.500 --> 00:16:42.580 align:middle line:84%
And we've already said one
cannot prove it, and, yet,

00:16:42.580 --> 00:16:45.520 align:middle line:84%
we ought to qualify
that, and publicly.

00:16:45.520 --> 00:16:47.470 align:middle line:90%
We cannot prove it.

00:16:47.470 --> 00:16:56.440 align:middle line:84%
But inwardly, to our self,
why we can modulate our life

00:16:56.440 --> 00:17:01.840 align:middle line:84%
to the point where that
view of the greatness,

00:17:01.840 --> 00:17:08.400 align:middle line:84%
the wonder, the awesomeness
of being does make sense.

00:17:08.400 --> 00:17:13.510 align:middle line:84%
But we repeat again, not
provable across the board

00:17:13.510 --> 00:17:14.470 align:middle line:90%
to everyone.

00:17:14.470 --> 00:17:22.210 align:middle line:84%
But individually, we can open
the eye of the soul, as Plato

00:17:22.210 --> 00:17:27.609 align:middle line:84%
would call it, the eye of the
heart, as the Sufis would call

00:17:27.609 --> 00:17:33.160 align:middle line:84%
it, the third eye of the
Tibetan, to the point

00:17:33.160 --> 00:17:40.660 align:middle line:84%
where we find ourselves
saying yes, yes, yes.

00:17:40.660 --> 00:17:44.800 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I think we're
living in a paradoxical age.

00:17:44.800 --> 00:17:49.150 align:middle line:84%
In your book, you bemoan to
some degree the scientism,

00:17:49.150 --> 00:17:53.590 align:middle line:84%
the skepticism, the lack
of faith and loss of faith.

00:17:53.590 --> 00:17:55.360 align:middle line:84%
And at the same time,
it seems there's

00:17:55.360 --> 00:17:58.550 align:middle line:84%
an incredible revival
of traditional,

00:17:58.550 --> 00:18:03.580 align:middle line:84%
and not just traditional, but
even mystical religious values.

00:18:03.580 --> 00:18:07.510 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I think
that that is true,

00:18:07.510 --> 00:18:15.340 align:middle line:84%
and one might say that I've
become aware of that in the two

00:18:15.340 --> 00:18:20.230 align:middle line:84%
years since I actually
completed writing the book.

00:18:20.230 --> 00:18:25.300 align:middle line:84%
And I find myself
more optimistic

00:18:25.300 --> 00:18:30.070 align:middle line:84%
than I was two years ago,
or maybe at any other time

00:18:30.070 --> 00:18:33.382 align:middle line:90%
in our life, that we may--

00:18:33.382 --> 00:18:37.180 align:middle line:84%
you might say this
view of existence

00:18:37.180 --> 00:18:42.220 align:middle line:84%
as meaningless has
kind of bottomed out.

00:18:42.220 --> 00:18:48.730 align:middle line:84%
We realized that that is
no philosophy to live by.

00:18:48.730 --> 00:18:53.500 align:middle line:84%
And so I do believe that there
is a new realization of that,

00:18:53.500 --> 00:18:58.890 align:middle line:84%
and people looking for roots
and where meaning lies.

00:18:58.890 --> 00:19:02.040 align:middle line:90%
>> Mm-hmm.

00:19:02.040 --> 00:19:05.460 align:middle line:84%
You refer, for example,
to Friedrich Nietzsche,

00:19:05.460 --> 00:19:09.030 align:middle line:84%
a 19th century
philosopher who, I think,

00:19:09.030 --> 00:19:12.510 align:middle line:84%
is probably the one who
originated the notion that God

00:19:12.510 --> 00:19:14.670 align:middle line:90%
is dead.

00:19:14.670 --> 00:19:17.940 align:middle line:84%
And you suggest, if I
understand correctly,

00:19:17.940 --> 00:19:21.070 align:middle line:84%
that in Nietzsche and other
philosophers like him,

00:19:21.070 --> 00:19:29.610 align:middle line:84%
Freud, Darwin, Marx, even there
is a sense of a turnaround.

00:19:29.610 --> 00:19:38.790 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I think the new and
late information regarding

00:19:38.790 --> 00:19:44.480 align:middle line:90%
Nietzsche does show that the--

00:19:44.480 --> 00:19:51.170 align:middle line:84%
even though he did
originate this allegory

00:19:51.170 --> 00:19:55.190 align:middle line:84%
of the mad man running
through the street saying--

00:19:55.190 --> 00:20:00.620 align:middle line:84%
shouting down, God is
dead, yet, behind it

00:20:00.620 --> 00:20:07.240 align:middle line:84%
all, he realized the
importance of that concept

00:20:07.240 --> 00:20:11.680 align:middle line:84%
and hoped that people
would not give it up,

00:20:11.680 --> 00:20:18.160 align:middle line:84%
even though, because his
own tragic personal life,

00:20:18.160 --> 00:20:21.860 align:middle line:84%
he found he could not
himself affirm it.

00:20:21.860 --> 00:20:25.270 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I don't want to
dwell on Nietzsche too much,

00:20:25.270 --> 00:20:27.582 align:middle line:90%
but I feel impelled to push--

00:20:27.582 --> 00:20:28.540 align:middle line:90%
>> He is an important--

00:20:28.540 --> 00:20:29.457 align:middle line:90%
>> --a little further.

00:20:29.457 --> 00:20:32.660 align:middle line:90%
He died, as I recall, insane.

00:20:32.660 --> 00:20:33.460 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:20:33.460 --> 00:20:35.620 align:middle line:84%
>> And towards the
end of his life,

00:20:35.620 --> 00:20:37.570 align:middle line:90%
he affirmed the death of God.

00:20:37.570 --> 00:20:38.740 align:middle line:90%
And, yet, I think--

00:20:38.740 --> 00:20:40.360 align:middle line:84%
I'm thinking of
Rudolf Steiner, who

00:20:40.360 --> 00:20:43.750 align:middle line:84%
I regard as one of the great
mystics of the 20th century,

00:20:43.750 --> 00:20:46.840 align:middle line:84%
who wrote a book, the
English translation of which

00:20:46.840 --> 00:20:49.900 align:middle line:84%
is "Friedrich Nietzsche,
Fighter for Freedom."

00:20:49.900 --> 00:20:51.550 align:middle line:90%
>> Uh-huh.

00:20:51.550 --> 00:20:53.680 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:20:53.680 --> 00:20:59.050 align:middle line:84%
There are these many strands
within Nietzsche's thought,

00:20:59.050 --> 00:21:02.790 align:middle line:84%
and almost as though there
are as many Nietzsches

00:21:02.790 --> 00:21:08.710 align:middle line:84%
as there are readers, and
very complex, so tremendously

00:21:08.710 --> 00:21:10.720 align:middle line:90%
powerful writing.

00:21:10.720 --> 00:21:15.550 align:middle line:84%
And, yes, one does find
those other strands there.

00:21:15.550 --> 00:21:18.220 align:middle line:84%
>> It strikes me
that in Nietzsche,

00:21:18.220 --> 00:21:21.880 align:middle line:84%
we see something of the
human spirit in our own age,

00:21:21.880 --> 00:21:22.810 align:middle line:90%
spreading out all--

00:21:22.810 --> 00:21:22.990 align:middle line:90%
>> That's a good--

00:21:22.990 --> 00:21:23.830 align:middle line:90%
>> --over the place.

00:21:23.830 --> 00:21:31.960 align:middle line:84%
>> --good point, and, of course,
his championing of strength

00:21:31.960 --> 00:21:34.600 align:middle line:90%
and the importance of strength.

00:21:34.600 --> 00:21:42.220 align:middle line:84%
Now, unfortunately, he said it
so nebulously or metaphorically

00:21:42.220 --> 00:21:46.420 align:middle line:84%
that it picked up
by the wrong end,

00:21:46.420 --> 00:21:49.810 align:middle line:84%
by the Nazis, and
interpreting this

00:21:49.810 --> 00:21:52.600 align:middle line:90%
in terms of physical strength.

00:21:52.600 --> 00:21:56.560 align:middle line:84%
Well, again, but you're
quite right in coming back

00:21:56.560 --> 00:21:59.740 align:middle line:84%
to him as a seminal
figure and one

00:21:59.740 --> 00:22:03.460 align:middle line:84%
of the most powerful and
also complex figures among--

00:22:03.460 --> 00:22:04.260 align:middle line:90%
during the--

00:22:04.260 --> 00:22:07.840 align:middle line:84%
>> There's a great irony, that
somebody who is considered

00:22:07.840 --> 00:22:11.710 align:middle line:84%
the spiritual father of
Nazism is also regarded

00:22:11.710 --> 00:22:14.980 align:middle line:84%
as the spiritual father of
great mystical movements,

00:22:14.980 --> 00:22:16.570 align:middle line:90%
authentically.

00:22:16.570 --> 00:22:19.400 align:middle line:84%
There is a fine
knife's edge here,

00:22:19.400 --> 00:22:23.940 align:middle line:84%
and maybe it represents
where we stand now, perhaps.

00:22:23.940 --> 00:22:24.790 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:22:24.790 --> 00:22:28.210 align:middle line:84%
Well, I'm glad you bring
in that comparison.

00:22:28.210 --> 00:22:32.675 align:middle line:84%
He remains a seminal
figure and also

00:22:32.675 --> 00:22:35.600 align:middle line:90%
a symbolic figure for our time.

00:22:35.600 --> 00:22:36.400 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:22:36.400 --> 00:22:39.505 align:middle line:84%
Huston, we could be
talking about this forever,

00:22:39.505 --> 00:22:41.252 align:middle line:84%
and I would love
to do that but--

00:22:41.252 --> 00:22:42.775 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:22:42.775 --> 00:22:45.130 align:middle line:84%
--we're running out
of time right now.

00:22:45.130 --> 00:22:48.040 align:middle line:84%
I know we've barely
scratched the surface

00:22:48.040 --> 00:22:51.490 align:middle line:84%
of this important discussion
on the human spirit.

00:22:51.490 --> 00:22:53.860 align:middle line:84%
Thank you so much,
Huston, for being with me.

00:22:53.860 --> 00:22:56.670 align:middle line:84%
>> So good to be
with you, Jeffrey.

00:22:56.670 --> 00:23:00.700 align:middle line:84%
>> And thank you
for being with us.

